CLASS
Avocado - an original Pacific Rim tropical fruit.
Native to South America, the avocado was first discovered by European chefs in the middle of the
nineteenth century. Now exported to the world by California, New Zealand and South Africa, it's a
new classic in modern sushi, and is an old favourite being given a new twist by today's chefs in
salads, omelettes and pasta dishes to name a few.
Our meal service offers you contemporary, brasserie-style cuisine alongside award winning Australasian wines.
Tony Adcock, from New Zealand's famous Harbourside Restaurant, helps to define the experience onboard.
He works with our team of dedicated chefs and consulting restaurants from around the world to develop
Pacific Rim inspired regional cuisine.
